    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix socket resource leak in GUI tracer module\n\n### Summary\nThe GUI tracer module in the OAI5G codebase was leaking socket file descriptors due to improper cleanup of X11 connections. When applications using the tracer GUI exited, the X connection created by `XOpenDisplay()` was never closed with `XCloseDisplay()`, leading to socket resource exhaustion over time.\n\nThis issue was particularly noticeable when using textlist widgets, as the `_textlist_add` function and related GUI operations would trigger frequent X server interactions without proper resource cleanup.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/gui/x.h`: Added `x_close()` function declaration and necessary includes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/gui/x.c`: Implemented `x_close()` function to properly cleanup X11 resources including fonts, colors, and the display connection\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/gui/gui.h`: Added `gui_cleanup()` function declaration and necessary includes  \n- `common/utils/T/tracer/gui/init.c`: Implemented `gui_cleanup()` function to properly cleanup GUI resources and call `x_close()`\n\nApplications should now call `gui_cleanup()` before exiting to prevent socket resource leaks. The fix ensures that `XCloseDisplay()` is properly called to close the X server connection socket.\n\n"
}